{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Inline 'Shadow this line' mini-drill on each AI message in conversation",
  "description": "Add a compact in-thread shadowing affordance to every assistant message in the live conversation, so users can immediately mimic and get pronunciation feedback on the AI's last line without leaving the chat or waiting until the post-conversation Shadowing exercise. Today, ShadowingExercise (frontend/src/components/conversation/ShadowingExercise.tsx) only appears in the post-conversation summary flow; users miss the moment of highest engagement (right after hearing the line). This proposal adds an inline path to listening+speaking practice, reinforcing pronunciation in tight loop and increasing perceived productivity during the conversation.\n\nWhat to build:\n1. New component frontend/src/components/conversation/InlineShadowButton.tsx — small icon button (Headphones+Mic) rendered inline at the bottom-right of each `.message-assistant` bubble in the conversation thread. Three states: idle, playing (TTS at 0.85x rate via useSpeechSynthesis), recording (mic via useSpeechRecognition with 6s auto-stop), and result (shows compact pronunciation score returned from api.evaluatePronunciation; expected_text = the AI sentence, transcript = mic result). Result is a small inline pill: 'Pronunciation: 82%' colored green/amber/red plus a Retry button. Errors fall back to a friendly inline message; never blocks the conversation.\n   - Pure helper `splitIntoShadowableLines(text: string): string[]` (sentence-split, keep lines 4-18 words; pick the first qualifying sentence as the shadow target). Export so it can be unit-tested without rendering.\n   - Props: `text: string`, optional `onComplete?: (score: number) => void`.\n   - Uses existing hooks; no new dependencies; no new backend endpoints.\n2. Integrate in frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx: render <InlineShadowButton text={msg.content} /> inside the assistant message bubble JSX (only when role === 'assistant' and content has at least one shadowable sentence). Keep it visually subtle (icon-only with tooltip 'Shadow this line') so it doesn't crowd the existing FeedbackPanel/GrammarNotesPanel UI. Hidden when ReplyProgressIndicator is shown for that bubble.\n3. Export from frontend/src/components/conversation/index.ts.\n4. Add unit test frontend/src/__tests__/InlineShadowButton.test.tsx covering: splitIntoShadowableLines (filters too-short/too-long sentences; returns empty for whitespace), button renders with aria-label='Shadow this line', clicking advances to playing state (mock useSpeechSynthesis), and result pill renders given a mock evaluation response.\n\nNon-goals: no DB schema changes, no backend changes, no new API. Keeps scope under 5 files. Verifiable via the new unit test plus existing Conversation.tsx tests (snapshot/integration unaffected because the button is additive).",
  "files_to_modify": [
    "frontend/src/components/conversation/InlineShadowButton.tsx",
    "frontend/src/components/conversation/index.ts",
    "frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx",
    "frontend/src/__tests__/InlineShadowButton.test.tsx"
  ],
  "priority": "medium",
