  "description": "PERF-HIGH backlog sub-item (3): introduce SSE/chunked streaming for the conversation assistant reply so the user sees text appear incrementally instead of waiting 6–16s for the full response. Most other PERF-HIGH sub-items (parallel LLM, warm pool, history truncation, Quick Reply) are done; streaming is the largest remaining win for perceived latency.\n\nScope (single iteration, ≤5 files):\n\n1. app/copilot_client.py — Add an async generator method `stream_chat(messages, ...)` that yields text chunks. The Copilot/OpenAI-style endpoint already supports `stream=True` via SSE `data:` lines; parse `delta.content` chunks and yield them. Keep the existing non-streaming `chat()` for grammar-check and other call sites unchanged.\n\n2. app/routers/conversation.py — Add a new endpoint `POST /api/conversation/{session_id}/message/stream` that returns `StreamingResponse` with `media_type=\"text/event-stream\"`. It performs the same prep as the existing `/message` endpoint (load session, build prompt, save user turn, optionally run grammar check in parallel via asyncio.gather) but streams the assistant reply token-by-token as `data: {\"type\":\"chunk\",\"text\":\"...\"}\\n\\n` events. After the stream completes, emit a final `data: {\"type\":\"done\",\"message_id\":..., \"grammar\":{...}}\\n\\n` event and persist the full assistant message to the DB via existing DAL functions. Keep the legacy non-streaming endpoint working for backward compat / tests. Log p50 first-chunk latency and total latency.\n\n3. frontend/src/api/conversation.ts (or equivalent) — Add `streamMessage(sessionId, text, { onChunk, onDone, onError })` using `fetch` + `ReadableStream` reader to parse SSE lines.\n\n4. frontend/src/components/Conversation/ConversationChat.tsx (or the component that calls sendMessage) — Use the streaming API: append an empty assistant bubble immediately, append chunks as they arrive (showing a blinking caret while streaming), then attach grammar feedback on `done`. Fall back to non-streaming endpoint on error.\n\n5. tests/integration/test_conversation_stream.py — New test using FastAPI TestClient to hit the stream endpoint with a mocked `stream_chat` async generator yielding 3 chunks; assert the response is `text/event-stream`, contains all 3 chunk events plus a `done` event, and that the assistant message is persisted to the DB after streaming finishes.\n\nNo schema changes required (reuses existing conversation_messages table). Success criterion: first chunk visible to user within ~1s in manual test; integration test passes.",
