  "description": "Add a 'Role-Swap Replay' mode that appears on the Conversation summary screen. After a user completes a conversation (chat phase ended, summary visible), they can tap a new 'Practice the other side' button to replay the conversation with roles reversed: the system plays back (TTS) what the user originally said, and the user must speak (or type) what the AI originally said. This trains listening comprehension of the user's own utterances AND active recall/production of well-formed AI English — a high-leverage drill that reuses content already familiar to the user.\n\nScope (≤5 files):\n\n1. **app/routers/conversation.py** — Add `GET /api/conversation/{conversation_id}/role-swap` endpoint that returns the ordered turn list as `{ turns: [{ index, original_speaker: 'user'|'assistant', text: str }] }`. Reuses existing message fetch in `app/dal/conversation.py` (e.g., `get_messages_for_conversation` or equivalent — verify name; otherwise add a thin DAL wrapper). System turns and any non-conversational metadata are filtered out. Response also includes `topic` and `language_level` for context. No schema changes.\n\n2. **frontend/src/api.ts** — Add `getRoleSwapScript(conversationId)` typed function and `RoleSwapTurn` / `RoleSwapScript` types.\n\n3. **frontend/src/components/conversation/RoleSwapReplay.tsx** (NEW) — Component that walks through turns one at a time. For each turn:\n   - If `original_speaker === 'user'`: auto-play TTS (use existing `speak()` util / browser SpeechSynthesis already used elsewhere) and show a 'Listened' Next button.\n   - If `original_speaker === 'assistant'`: show a 'Reveal' button that hides the target text initially, plus a mic record button (reuse existing SpeechRecognition hook pattern from `Pronunciation.tsx` / `EchoPractice.tsx`) so the user attempts the line, then can compare with the revealed target text. Also a 'Skip' / 'Next' button.\n   - Progress indicator (turn N of M) and a 'Finish' button at the end that returns to the summary.\n\n4. **frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx** — On the summary phase, add a 'Practice the other side' button that toggles a new `roleSwapMode` state and renders `<RoleSwapReplay conversationId={...} onClose={...} />` inline (or as a modal overlay following existing modal patterns in the file). Add appropriate i18n keys (`roleSwapButton`, `roleSwapTitle`, `roleSwapListenPrompt`, `roleSwapSpeakPrompt`, `roleSwapReveal`, `roleSwapNext`, `roleSwapFinish`).\n\n5. **frontend/src/i18n/I18nContext.tsx** (or wherever translations live — verify path; likely `frontend/src/i18n/`) — Add the new keys for both `en` and `ja`.\n\nWhy high-value: (a) directly serves listening + speaking, the app's stated focus; (b) zero new content cost — it remixes data the user just generated, so each replay is uniquely personalized; (c) increases time-on-task and retention without LLM round-trips (no Copilot calls beyond the original fetch); (d) complements the recently shipped shadowing/replay UX line of work without duplicating it (those are sentence-level; this is dialogue-level).\n\nTesting: add a small unit test for the new endpoint in `tests/integration/` covering happy path and 404 for nonexistent conversation; component-level testing optional given scope.",
